<p><a name="UW"></a><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="4"><b>University of Wisconsin</b></font><br>
<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="2"><b>By Bill Schmitz</b></font></P>

<P><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3">MADISON, Wis.-- About 350 University of Wisconsin-Madison students and workers took over the state capitol rotunda on April 4. Students are angry that the governor's budget proposal calls for a 6 percent tuition hike and cutting funds for diversity programs. Chanting "Students and workers unite," students marched to the Capitol where they joined 300 state workers protesting the governor's proposed 1 percent pay increase.</P>



